 Just thought I'd proffer the following for your consideration before the big event this weekend, in support of us caster classes:<br><br>A) Casters have nowhere near the AC, HP and Dmg ability of melee classes, when going toe-to-toe, so not allowing them to buff themselves and med up before combat would be voluntary manslaughter.<br><br>2) Casters have no chance of winning in combat against melee classes if they are not allowed to use spells at all once combat begins.<br><br>D) How about considering the following two options for casters v. melee in the Arena: <br>     1. Casters are allowed to buff themselves all they want, but cannot med prior to combat.  Casters may use <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ANY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spells they choose during the combat.<br>     2. Casters may buff themselves and med completely prior to combat, but they may <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NOT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> use any movement reducing spells (root, snare, etc) during combat.  Attack slowing spells would still be allowed, but movement reducing spells would be grounds for disqualification.<br><br>Just my 2cp, but something for your consideration for the event.<br><br>On a different topic, I completed the quest for the Ivy Etched Helm, which Balderak is now proudly wearing.  I want to heartily thank Mollybell for her help with this quest.  It would have been nearly impossible for me to do without her.  I am still working on the Ivy Etched Leggings and Gauntlets quests.  If anyone wants to help with those, just let me know.  Molly and I had lots of fun, and got a few pp in the process.  I hope to see you all at the tourney.<br><br>All Hail Pax Familla !!<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mazatlan Hazatan, Druid</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Druid Officer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://kickme.to/paxfamilla">Pax Familla</a><!--EZCO